157
00:06:52,610 --> 00:06:54,150
I understand. We'll leave right away.

158
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,400
Let's go eat inside.

159
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:56,840
- Yes, yes.
- No, no.

160
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:57,700
Leader, please.

161
00:06:57,710 --> 00:06:59,510
- Leader, please.
- No need.

162
00:06:59,730 --> 00:07:01,370
Leader, let's eat inside.

163
00:07:01,370 --> 00:07:02,610
Let's go together for a bite.

164
00:07:02,610 --> 00:07:03,960
- No need.
- Leader, this way.

165
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:04,800
- No.
- Let's go.

166
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,310
I have something to do.

167
00:07:06,930 --> 00:07:07,770
Something to do?

168
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:09,570
- Yes, I have to go.
- Look at this.

169
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:10,560
- Bye.
- Bad timing.

170
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,460
I'll leave you to it.

171
00:07:11,690 --> 00:07:12,540
You go ahead.

172
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:14,870
Ms. Tang, take care.

173
00:07:15,280 --> 00:07:16,190
Uncle Wang.

174
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:22,980
This is so awkward.

175
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,360
Why run so fast?

176
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:26,190
I just reprimanded him today,

177
00:07:26,610 --> 00:07:27,780
and then just now...

178
00:07:28,050 --> 00:07:29,660
I'm so embarrassed.

179
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:32,130
Come on, leader, sit here.

180
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:33,100
Let's eat here.

181
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,170
- I'm here.
- Come on.

182
00:07:34,170 --> 00:07:35,100
You're so annoying.

183
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:37,070
I'll hit you, really.

184
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:39,930
Don't be embarrassed.

185
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:40,980
He'll be embarrassed.

186
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:42,390
I'm embarrassed.

187
00:07:44,690 --> 00:07:45,530
Yang.

188
00:07:46,490 --> 00:07:47,870
Do you remember?

189
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:50,580
That's our secret passage from before.

190
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,640
If we were running late,
we would take that alley.

191
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,070
Of course, I remember.

192
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:56,850
How many times have we been able

193
00:07:56,850 --> 00:07:57,880
to reach class on time

194
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,680
thanks to this secret passage

195
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,220
before the teacher checked?

196
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,960
Those fools in the next class

197
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,070
even asked me,

198
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:05,770
"How strange."

199
00:08:05,770 --> 00:08:06,610
"How come you guys"

200
00:08:06,610 --> 00:08:07,640
"can always make it,"

201
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:08,730
"but we always"

202
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:09,980
"get deducted points?"

203
00:08:10,370 --> 00:08:11,250
I explained the reason

204
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,540
to them clearly.

205
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:13,780
What did you say?

206
00:08:14,810 --> 00:08:16,310
I said, "You know who Yang is?"

207
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:17,570
"You know her background?"

208
00:08:17,570 --> 00:08:18,440
"We can get away."

209
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,400
What is my background?

210
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,390
You tell me.

211
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:21,360
You are...

212
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,730
Come, leader, let's eat.

213
00:08:23,730 --> 00:08:24,730
Jiang Shiyan.

214
00:08:24,730 --> 00:08:25,680
Really.

215
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,980
I discovered it.

216
00:08:27,370 --> 00:08:29,610
Sometimes you're not even human.

217
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:30,480
Jiang Shiyan,

218
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,520
you're always so annoying.

219
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,050
You really live up to your name.

220
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:34,490
Outstandingly annoying.

221
00:08:34,490 --> 00:08:35,900
Of course. We're buddies.

222
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:37,700
Birds of a feather flock together.

223
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:42,970
Upset? Where are you going?

224
00:08:42,970 --> 00:08:44,540
I'm going to check the secret passage.

225
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:50,180
(Be careful)

226
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:53,900
These alleys haven't changed at all.

227
00:08:58,610 --> 00:09:00,050
This painting is still here.

228
00:09:00,050 --> 00:09:01,800
(Harvest)
Exactly the same. Didn't change.

229
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:02,780
(Flowers)
That chili.

230
00:09:08,450 --> 00:09:10,060
I remember right here,

231
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:12,020
in our second or third year...

232
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:13,210
The second year.

233
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,660
I bought fried chicken with someone.

234
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:18,530
When we were about to eat

235
00:09:18,530 --> 00:09:19,770
in this alley,

236
00:09:19,770 --> 00:09:21,300
we encountered a dog.

237
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,730
He ran away in a panic,

238
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:26,180
and the dog chased after him.

239
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,230
And he ran even faster.

240
00:09:28,370 --> 00:09:29,610
I said, "Don't run!"

241
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:31,250
"Take the fried chicken!"

242
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:32,850
"I'll throw a stone at it!"

243
00:09:32,850 --> 00:09:34,450
Just as I gave him the chicken,

244
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:35,290
what did he do?

245
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:37,470
He threw it away!

246
00:09:38,370 --> 00:09:39,750
You know what?

247
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,470
You're 1.8 meters tall

248
00:09:42,090 --> 00:09:44,230
with a courage of 1.8 mm.

249
00:09:46,370 --> 00:09:47,820
You also ran away.

250
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:50,010
I ran because you ran, alright?

251
00:09:50,010 --> 00:09:51,470
I wouldn't have run if you hadn't.

252
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:52,490
Let the past

253
00:09:52,490 --> 00:09:53,820
be the past.

254
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:57,170
That dog is probably

255
00:09:57,170 --> 00:09:58,510
in the afterlife now.

256
00:09:59,040 --> 00:09:59,880
But

257
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:01,990
if I had the chance

258
00:10:02,130 --> 00:10:03,270
to reunite with it...

259
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:04,400
What would you do?

260
00:10:04,610 --> 00:10:06,510
I wouldn't just run away.

261
00:10:07,090 --> 00:10:08,420
I'd confront it

262
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:10,300
face to face.

263
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,480
This...

264
00:10:12,130 --> 00:10:13,150
What are you doing?

265
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,180
You said it.

266
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:16,150
You met it again.

267
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,900
Didn't you just say...

268
00:10:27,450 --> 00:10:29,940
Yang, it's okay.

269
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:32,630
I'm here to protect you.

270
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:38,350
Normally, I would be...

271
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,110
I wouldn't be scared.

272
00:10:41,490 --> 00:10:42,560
But Yang, look at it.

273
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,900
Its ears are up.

274
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,300
It's a mad dog!

275
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:48,610
Not necessarily.

276
00:10:48,610 --> 00:10:50,470
I think its emotions are quite stable.

277
00:10:51,370 --> 00:10:52,650
Yang, you can't joke

278
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:53,520
with your life.

279
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:54,450
Really?

280
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,290
Yes.

281
00:10:55,850 --> 00:10:58,420
So what to do? Should we run?

282
00:10:58,640 --> 00:10:59,590
I'll protect you.

283
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:01,780
You run first.

284
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,660
I'll cover you.

285
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,450
Yang, you're running so fast!

286
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:07,420
